50|$|In 1860 {{a provincial}} law passed. Before the Ottoman <b>Electoral</b> <b>Law,</b> provincial law {{included}} {{elections for the}} neighborhood headmen. It is arguable that elections in the Ottoman Empire began in 1860, not 1876. Registration was the task of village and neighborhood headmen and religious leaders, which this rule extended to Ottoman <b>Electoral</b> <b>Law.</b> In this respect at the lowest level, basic election unit, never changed.|$|R
